  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Market linkage and improving extension services</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Isoka District Rice Association (IDRA) was formed in 2009, by representatives of more than 700 rice farmers. Currently the organisation counts 1466 members. The vision of IDRA is to improve the capacity of rice farmers in the district and assit them in making their farms profitable businesses. The association wishes to create value for its members through continued provision of a number of business development services such as extension, training, input supply, marketing, warehouse facilities, finance and other services. The 2013 project of IDRA aims to continue improving the capacity of rice farmers in the district and enable IDRA to operate as profitable business through provision of business development services. An office and secretariat was established in previous year and services are being developed and improved for farmers. In 2012 a business plan was developed in which it is stated that IDRA has to find capital investment to build warehouses and trade finance, in 2013 IDRA plans to materialize some of the plans. Agriterra supports IDRA in its organisational capacity development among others through group formation with the objective to establish cooperatives, IDRA makes use of the Enabling Rural Inovation tool developed for this purpose.

The main aim of IDRA is to increase income and employment among its members, thereby reducing poverty and increasing the social and economic conditions and livelihood of it members through the following objectives:
&#x2022;	To promoting production processing distribution marketing and consumption of rice and rice by product
&#x2022;	Promoting research in rice sub-sector in order to improve growth and consumption of rice and rice by products
&#x2022;	Encouraging rice value chain members to acquire knowledge, skill and information so as to improve their performance in order to reach the goal of self sustenance  in relatively short period of time
&#x2022;	Cooperating and collaborating with government and other organization towards achieving the goal of increasing income and employment among rice value chain members  so as to reduce poverty and improve their social and economic condition and livelihood
&#x2022;	Acquiring any freehold, leasehold property or things whatsoever which may be necessary and conveniently used to enhance the value of IDRA properties 
&#x2022;	Arranging insurance against loss, damage or liability of the association by the way of fire, theft ,accident or otherwise 
&#x2022;	Contributing cash in kind in support of under privileged and vulnerable members of the society
&#x2022;	Improve coordination of rice farming activities making it easier to mainstream HIV/AIDs, Gender, Youth and environmental conservation program

-	To develop a business plan for work capital and mobilize the required finance
-	To improve the supply chain management and business relation with PCS
-	To improve output marketing performance by 25-50%
-	To establish and meet the contract with Asela Malt Factory</narrative>
  </description>
